description.plain:
Laufey (pronounced lāy-vāy) is a 24-year-old Los Angeles-based singer, composer, producer and multi-instrumentalist whose jazz songs are about young love and self-discovery. Raised between Reykjavík and Washington, D.C. with annual visits to Beijing, the Icelandic-Chinese artist grew up playing cello as well as piano and became hooked on the jazz standards of Ella Fitzgerald after digging through her father’s record collection.

In 2020, while still a student at Berklee College of Music, Laufey released her debut single “Street by Street,” which went on to top the Icelandic radio charts. Following the release of her 2021 EP Typical of Me, Laufey was named Best New Artist in Jazz and Blues at the Icelandic Music Awards and hosted her own show on BBC Radio 3/BBC Sounds. Her debut full-length album Everything I Know About Love, debuted at #1 on Billboard’s Alternative New Artist Album chart, and the lead single “Valentine” peaked at #1 on the Spotify Jazz Chart. In 2022, Laufey was the most streamed jazz artist on Spotify, with 425 million streams across all platforms.

No matter how hard you try to create a distance, the bond seems impossible to break. With a remarkably powerful build-up to each chorus to an ethereal bridge, Laufey’s lyrics and gorgeous melody seals the deal to another beautifully told story that is easily relatable.

description.plain:
“Let You Break My Heart Again” is a single release featuring the Philharmonia Orchestra. Initially released on August 13th, 2021, the track marked Laufey’s first official collaboration with another artist/group.

The official video release of the song features Laufey as the lead vocalist and cellist for the song, featuring the Philharmonia Orchestra for additional instrumentation.



Lyrically, the song conveys melancholic undertones regarding love. Laufey describes herself in an unhappy relationship, and, despite her lover’s tendencies to leave her heartbroken and sad, she continues to allow them back into her life due to her enduring feelings for them. Despite this, she assures the listener that she will eventually stop falling in love with them someday.

songs.full_title: Valentine by Laufey
songs.title: Valentine

description.plain:
Released as a surprise drop on Valentine’s Day of 2022, “Valentine” was the lead single for Laufey’s debut album “Everything I Know About Love.”

The song details a sudden relationship that Laufey fell into without warning. Laufey described the song as:

A jazzy little song that I wrote about kind of falling in love for the first time and not really knowing how to feel or how to act.

Laufey has also noted that the overall songwriting and soundscape of the track ties into its lyrical content:

“Valentine” has this funny, off, almost-drunk pacing to it. The last line: “I blinked and suddenly I found a Valentine”, is a resolution. It’s holding for a time, and then it resolves in the end. That resolution feels very satisfying, it feels like something finishing or something making sense.

songs.full_title: Bewitched by Laufey
songs.title: Bewitched

description.plain:
“Bewitched” is the title track of Laufey’s official sophomore album. In an instant, the song sets a stage that appears somehow more magical than the album’s other accompanying singles. The dreamy instrumentals, romantic chord progression, and of course her timeless vocal tone actively casts a spell over the listener. Laufey never fails to encapsulate each emotion she wishes to convey through her impeccable story-like lyrics. Through Bewitched, she introduces a tale of new love and expresses the feelings of passion, hesitancy, and just how bewildering the experience could be.
“This all consuming, fire fuming
Cursing at the moon and losing”
Laufey’s lyricism throughout the song beautifully paints a picture for each listener, allowing anyone to relate their own unique experiences to each lyric, making the song all the more wonderful.

First performed on February 21, 2024, at the Brussels, Belgium stop of The Bewitched Tour, and “Goddess” would continue to be performed at her tour stops in Hamburg, Stockholm, Copenhagen, Berlin, Milan, Lausanne, Cologne, and Amsterdam.

Laufey announced the release of “Goddess” as a single on February 27, 2024, with twenty second snippets of the song uploaded on social media platforms such as Instagram and TikTok while concertgoers uploaded videos of her performing the song live.

Letter To My 13 Year Old Self, the 13th track on Bewitched, has Laufey using her lower register to deliver a musical letter to her teenage self. “Keep on going with your silly dream – Life is prettier than it may seem” she sings over a subtle accompaniment.

At the same time, the singer describes how she felt different from other girls her age.

Pretty little blonde girls around me were having their first kisses and whispering together in gym class. I just remember feeling so incredibly out of place and different.

via Vogue.

The track was first teased on TikTok.

songs.title: Second Best

description.plain:
Second Best, the second track on Laufey’s sophomore album Bewitched, was initially written on a fan’s request on TikTok.

The meaning of this song is very straight forward: being someone’s “second best,” while they are your “everything.” While knowing she is only this person’s second best, it is still hard for her to let go and move on from them:

“Why am I still wondering if I stand a chance or if you’d have me back?”
“I’m still a little in love with this mess”

While Dreamer opens the album with Chordettes-style vocal harmonies leading into a bittersweet shuffle, Second Best follows with a stripped-back arrangement.

description.plain:
On November 14, 2023, Laufey made her Spotify Singles debut with a cover of “Winter Wonderland” by Bing Crosby. The track was released as a Spotify exclusive as apart of their yearly Spotify Singles Holiday Collection.

The track features a composition similar to the original, with orchestral and jazz elements at the forefront and holiday elements such as jingle bells in the background.

On December 15, 2023, Laufey released the track on the rest of the streaming platforms as a part of her “12 Days of Christmas” event, removing the Spotify Singles branding on every platform besides Spotify.
